{
  "stem": "39.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We walked to the school, everyone just staring at you like you would have come from another planet, and you were exactly the same person whom you were just one day before.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Well, I was sort of lucky, because two girls from my class, non-Jewish girls, Christian girls, they decided that sometimes they will come to our house so I can walk with them to the school so I will feel less embarrassed.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And that meant a lot.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We were already in the last year of high school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Everyone was getting ready to the graduation, how it's going to be.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And, of course, we couldn't think too much about that, because we had other problems being Jew and not knowing what to expect.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Well, the newest thing, newest regulation, it was that they would start in the ghettos in our cities too.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "This came out, the new law, end of April, 1944.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Well, I knew-- we knew that graduation will be in May, end of May.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And somehow we applied in school that maybe we can graduate earlier than the rest of the class.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And it was allowed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we graduated earlier than everyone else, the written test, the verbal exam.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was end of April when we did that, because already May the 3rd, they took us into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The ghetto, at that time, it has an absolutely different meaning what we think a ghetto is today.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a part of a residential area in the city.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, it was gated all around.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And all around the gates, all the time, heavily armed soldiers and police.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They picked us up to take us into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't go by ourselves.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
